BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Surf's Up
DTSTART:20260511T082400
DTEND:20260511T164800
DESCRIPTION:TIDES:\n-2.976ft at 08:24\n-2.926ft at 16:48\n\nOBSERVATION:\n
 <strong>Dawn to 10:00AM:</strong> Long-period SSW Southern Hemi peaks\, wh
 ile and shorter-period NW/WNW swell mix holds\, maintaining waist-chest-sh
 oulder high waves\, as summertime standouts hit a foot+ overhead on favora
 ble tides. Light/variable winds through the morning\,\n\n<strong>Afternoon
  Outlook:</strong> Light+ SW afternoon onshores for some texture. Late aft
 ernoon/early evening high tide slows tide sensitive breaks. 
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Surf's Up
DTSTART:20260512T093000
DTEND:20260512T170000
DESCRIPTION:TIDES:\n-2.939ft at 09:30\n-2.977ft at 17:00\n\nOBSERVATION:\n
 Holding blend of long-period SSW Southern Hemi and shorter-period NW/WNW s
 well mix keeps many spots in waist-chest high+ waves\, as summertime stand
 outs see sets going a foot+ overhead on favorable tides. \n\nLight/variabl
 e winds through the morning\, turning light+ SW onshore for the afternoon.
  Late afternoon/evening high tides bog down tide sensitive spots. 
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Surf's Up
DTSTART:20260513T060600
DTEND:20260513T064200
DESCRIPTION:TIDES:\n-2.526ft at 06:06\n-2.951ft at 06:42\n\nOBSERVATION:\n
 Easing mix of SSW Southern Hemi and NW/WNW swell for mainly thigh to stoma
 ch high surf. Tide sensitive spots will be slowed by mid morning high tide
 \, then ebbing tide helps through mid day. \n\nLight/variable winds due mu
 ch of the morning\, followed by a light+ SW afternoon sea breeze. The onsh
 ores ease by the evening.
END:VEVENT
